{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01BNESPXdT1U91sPPU9gpbye", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confirmed \u2014 no `openshift-` prefix check. I need to add it.\n\nHere's my complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Files to modify\n\n### 1. `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go`\n\nAdd `strings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"openshift-\")` to the `shouldIgnorePod` method.\n\n**Change at line 427-443:**\n\n```go\n// shouldIgnorePod returns true if the pod should be ignored by the operator.\n// The operator should ignore the pods in the following cases:\n// - the pod is in the same namespace as the operator\n// - the pod is in a namespace with prefix kube-\n// - the pod is in a namespace with prefix openshift-\n// - the pod has a node name set\n// - the pod has a node selector that matches the control plane nodes\n// - the pod is owned by a DaemonSet\n// - the pod has required architecture affinity configured AND:\n//   - preferred affinity is already configured, OR\n//   - both CPPC and all matching PPCs have the NodeAffinityScoring plugin disabled\nfunc (pod *Pod) shouldIgnorePod(cppc *v1beta1.ClusterPodPlacementConfig, matchingPPCs []v1beta1.PodPlacementConfig) bool {\n\treturn utils.Namespace() == pod.Namespace || strings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"kube-\") ||\n\t\tstrings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"openshift-\") ||\n\t\tpod.Spec.NodeName != \"\" || pod.HasControlPlaneNodeSelector() || pod.IsFromDaemonSet() ||\n\t\tpod.isNodeSelectorConfiguredForArchitecture() &&\n\t\t\t(pod.isPreferredAffinityConfiguredForArchitecture() ||\n\t\t\t\t(!cppc.PluginsEnabled(common.NodeAffinityScoringPluginName) && !pod.hasMatchingPPCWithPlugin(matchingPPCs)))\n}\n```\n\n### 2. `internal/controller/podplacement/suite_test.go`\n\nAdd `\"openshift-kube-apiserver\"` to the `EnsureNamespaces` call so the namespace exists in the test environment.\n\n**Change at line 306:**\n\n```go\n\ttestingutils.EnsureNamespaces(ctx, k8sClient, \"openshift-config\", \"test-namespace\", \"openshift-kube-apiserver\")\n```\n\n### 3. `internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook_test.go`\n\nAdd the new Context block. The full updated file:\n\n```go\npackage podplacement\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\timgspecv1 \"github.com/opencontainers/image-spec/specs-go/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/image/fake/registry\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Internal/Controller/PodPlacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook\", func() {\n\tWhen(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\", func() {\n\t\tContext(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should ignore pods with a non-empty nodeName\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"test-namespace\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeName(\"test-node-name\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t\tContext(\"is handling a pod in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should not assign the scheduling gate even when the ClusterPodPlacementConfig namespaceSelector matches all namespaces\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).NotTo(ContainElement(corev1.PodSchedulingGate{\n\t\t\t\t\tName: utils.SchedulingGateName,\n\t\t\t\t}), \"pod in openshift-kube-apiserver should not have the scheduling gate\")\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n### 4. `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model_test.go`\n\nThe existing unit tests for `shouldIgnorePod` should also be updated. Look for the test table around line 1050 and add a test case for `openshift-kube-apiserver`. Find the section near line 1054 (`kube-system` test case):\n\nAdd this test case after the `\"pod in the kube- namespace\"` entry (after line 1057):\n\n```go\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"pod in the openshift- namespace\",\n\t\t\tfields: fields{\n\t\t\t\tPod: NewPod().WithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").Build(),\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twant: true,\n\t\t},\n```\n\nAnd also in the `shouldIgnorePod` table tests (around line 1969), add after the `\"pod in kube-system should be ignored\"` entry (after line 1978):\n\n```go\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"pod in openshift-kube-apiserver should be ignored\",\n\t\t\tpod:  NewPod().WithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").Build(),\n\t\t\tcppc: NewClusterPodPlacementConfig().\n\t\t\t\tWithName(common.SingletonResourceObjectName).\n\t\t\t\tWithNodeAffinityScoring(true).\n\t\t\t\tWithNodeAffinityScoringTerm(utils.ArchitectureAmd64, 50).\n\t\t\t\tBuild(),\n\t\t\tmatchingPPCs: []v1beta1.PodPlacementConfig{},\n\t\t\twant:         true, // Should ignore - openshift system namespace\n\t\t},\n```\n\n---\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-baseline\n\n# Verify it compiles\ngo build ./...\n\n# Run the specific unit tests\ngo test ./internal/controller/podplacement/... -run TestPod -count=1\n\n# Run the integration tests (requires envtest binaries)\nmake test\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of changes\n\n**4 files modified:**\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go:438` | Add `strings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"openshift-\")` to `shouldIgnorePod` so pods in `openshift-*` namespaces (including `openshift-kube-apiserver`) are excluded from scheduling gate assignment |\n| `internal/controller/podplacement/suite_test.go:306` | Add `\"openshift-kube-apiserver\"` to `EnsureNamespaces` so the namespace exists in the test environment |\n| `internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook_test.go` | Add new Context block with an It spec that creates a pod in `openshift-kube-apiserver` and asserts the scheduling gate is NOT present |\n| `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model_test.go` | Add unit test cases for `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace in the `shouldIgnorePod` test tables |\n\nThe core logic change is adding `strings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"openshift-\")` to `shouldIgnorePod`. This ensures that pods in any `openshift-*` namespace \u2014 including critical control-plane namespaces like `openshift-kube-apiserver` \u2014 are never gated, matching the existing exclusion pattern for `kube-*` namespaces."}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1183, "cache_read_input_tokens": 71324, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1183, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 3}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "7656ed6b-0e61-49df-8391-bae83978b510", "uuid": "2088dd19-040e-44ad-b06b-a6b22cafca52", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011Cd3uzeYJZ3SPNaLi9WmGx", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T13:23:09.161Z"}
